Project Moocs development log:

2014.4.1
1.development environment:
    use ruby 2.0.0 and rails 4.0.0: $ rvm use 2.0.0

2.create project moocs
    $ rails new moocs
    $ git init
    $ git add .
    $ git status
    $ git commit -m 'Project MOOCS started now!'

3.create course model
    $ rails generate scaffold Course code:string name:string description:text length:integer image_url:string start_time:date source_url:string audit_status:boolean
    $ rake db:migrate

4.add paperclip plugin
    installation: imagemagick, and modify Gemfile, and run bundle install
    $ rails generate migration add_course_image_to_courses
    write up and down method
    $ rake db:migrate
    modify course.rb: has_attachment_file file stored at public/system/... (you have to create a new directory name system under directory public)
    ! A hole for attack

